@startuml
title PB-158 UC8 SQD: Get campaigns customer is eligible for

actor "Next Customer" as NextCustomer
participant "P&O\n(Core Next)" as PnOCN #lightblue#white
database "P&O DB" as PO_DB #grey#black
rectangle CoreBradesco { participant "Core Bradesco"} 

note over 0,-24 : <b>Abstract:</b>\nThe endpoint will be modified so that it can \ncalled by the user and return list of\ncampaigns they are eligable to.\na campaign logo version number returned,\nas well as a campagin logo image(if requested).


box "" 
    note right of NextCustomer:<u><font color=red size="3">Endpoint</font></u>: GET /campaigns
    
<u><font color=green size="3"><i>Current implementation</i>:</font></u> Currently called by system management returns all campsaigns with option specify:\n* NAME\n * PARTNER_ID\n * OFFER_ID 
    
<b><u><font color=purple >Required Implementation</font></u></b>: Either through extension or new API enable users call this end point returning their eligibility status along optional field indicating whether offer should include logos too! As part response from CAMPAIGN_RETRIEVAL add these fields - Campaign Logo Version Number & Optional Image itself IF REQUESTED BY USER!! ENSURE BACKWARDS COMPATIBILITY MAINTAINED AT ALL TIMES!!!    
end box



== Step One ==
activate NextCustomer  
->PO_CN:GetCampaignUserEligible({NAME},{PARTNERID},ACTIVE,{OFFRID})  

frame filterOn{filter on} do   
   ->CN:getCampUsrElibltyStatus(...)     
